@yajiedesign I know, but sometimes you need an arbitrary matrix. 

For example, when using Spatial Transformer Networks, there's a subnet that computes an affine transform matrix. If I want to, say, force this matrix to be diagonal without touching the STN code, I could just do a broadcast_mul between the output of the subnet and a mask, [1 0 0 1 0 0]. 

With the symbolic API as it is I see no way to do this except using a Variable and bind.

